---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Halloween — Horror Terms That Score Big"
  description="Halloween and horror words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. ZOMBIE (19pts), GHOUL (9pts), CRYPT (12pts), WITCH (13pts). Spooky vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble halloween words, zombie scrabble points, ghoul scrabble, crypt scrabble, witch scrabble word, horror terms scrabble, spooky words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Halloween — Horror Terms That Score Big","description":"Halloween and horror words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. ZOMBIE (19pts), GHOUL (9pts), CRYPT (12pts), WITCH (13pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-halloween"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is ZOMBIE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! ZOMBIE scores 19 points (Z=10, O=1, M=3, B=3, I=1, E=1). The Z tile alone contributes over half the score. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play GHOUL in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. GHOUL scores 9 points (G=2, H=4, O=1, U=1, L=1) as a 5-letter word. It means a spirit that robs graves. Valid in all official Scrabble dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CRYPT valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! CRYPT scores 12 points (C=3, R=1, Y=4, P=3, T=1) as a 5-letter word with no vowels except Y. It's useful for consonant-heavy racks and valid in competitive play."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Halloween — Horror Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Halloween vocabulary is a goldmine for Scrabble players. Horror, supernatural, and gothic terms are loaded with Z, W, H, and Y tiles — high-value letters that deliver big scores when placed strategically. From zombies to crypts, these spooky words pack serious punch.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZOMBIE (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WITCH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CRYPT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GHOUL</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Horror Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">ZOMBIE — 19 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Z=10, O=1, M=3, B=3, I=1, E=1 · 6 letters · Uses Z tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">An undead creature from Haitian folklore. ZOMBIE gets its power from Z=10 plus M=3 and B=3, delivering 19 points from 6 tiles. On a double-word square, that's 38 points from a single common word.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧙 WITCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · W=4, I=1, T=1, C=3, H=4 · Sorceress</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚰️ CRYPT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · C=3, R=1, Y=4, P=3, T=1 · Underground vault</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👻 GHOUL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · G=2, H=4, O=1, U=1, L=1 · Grave spirit</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦇 FRIGHT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · F=4, R=1, I=1, G=2, H=4, T=1 · Sudden fear</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Supernatural Creatures</h2>
      <p>Gothic monsters and supernatural beings provide some of the most flavourful Scrabble words:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WRAITH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PHANTOM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SPECTRE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FIEND</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GOBLIN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GHASTLY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dark and Gothic Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕯️ EERIE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · E=1, E=1, R=1, I=1, E=1 · Uncanny</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💀 MACABRE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · M=3, A=1, C=3, A=1, B=3, R=1, E=1 · Gruesome</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌑 GLOOMY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · G=2, L=1, O=1, O=1, M=3, Y=4 · Dark/dreary</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕸️ COBWEB</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · C=3, O=1, B=3, W=4, E=1, B=3 · Spider silk</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Halloween Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZOMBIE is your best Z-word for 6 tiles:</span> At 19 points from 6 common tiles, ZOMBIE outscores most Z words. The M+B consonant pair makes it playable on tight boards.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CRYPT has no standard vowels:</span> When your rack is vowel-starved, CRYPT (12pts) uses C, R, Y, P, T — all consonants (Y acts as vowel). Perfect for consonant-heavy situations.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WITCH hooks to BEWITCH:</span> WITCH (13pts) can be extended with BE- to create BEWITCH (17pts). Play WITCH near the left edge and plan the hook for your next turn.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Halloween words leverage <span class="text-white font-medium">high-value consonant clusters</span> — Z in ZOMBIE, W+H in WITCH and WRAITH, C+Y+P in CRYPT. They also excel at using double-B (COBWEB, GOBLIN) when you're stuck with two B tiles.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-no-vowels/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words with No Vowels</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid spooky word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
